  "texts": [
    "For a turn i, an outcome o i is an indicator variable that is true if the customer has explicitly stated their intended behavior within messages c 1, m 1,.",
    ", c i, and this behavior aligns with the business's desired actions (such as purchasing a product/service or sharing contact information).",
    "In practice, o i can be predicted by a classifier or manually reported by the business.",
    "There is a significant body of literature focused on the so-called single-turn setting: here, the focus is on selecting the next best response, rather than optimizing for long-term outcomes across multiple dialogue turns.",
    "In fact, many real-world chatbots optimize single-turn objectives (Irvine et al., 2023; Han et al., 2025)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "In fact, many real-world chatbots optimize single-turn objectives (Irvine et al., 2023; Han et al., 2025)."
  ]
